            <div class="w3-card w3-margin-right w3-margin-left w3-margin-top">
                <div id="question_one" class="w3-container w3-light-grey" style="cursor: pointer;"><h5>How does the Coronavirus spread?</h5></div>
                <div id="answer_one" class="w3-container" hidden="true">
                    <p>Covid-19 spreads most commonly from person-to-person contact when people are in close quarters with each other. Some infections may also be spread through airborne transmission, though data indicates close contact is the much more common cause. Also less commonly then close person-to-person contact transmission, contact with contaminated surfaces is another way that the virus can move between people. Finally, Covid-19 can spread between people and animals, though the risk for this has been determined to be quite low. </p>
                    <p>For more detailed information, please visit the <a href="https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/prevent-getting-sick/how-covid-spreads.html" target="_blank">CDC website</a>.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
                
            <div class="w3-card w3-margin-right w3-margin-left w3-margin-top">
                <div id="question_two" class="w3-container w3-light-grey" style="cursor: pointer;"><h5>What types of symptoms does Covid-19 cause?</h5></div>
                <div id="answer_two" class="w3-container" hidden="true">
                    <p>Healthcare professionals have identified a wide array of symptoms cause by Covid-19. This list includes, but is not limited to the following:</p>
                    <ul class="w3-ul w3-border">
                        <li>Fever</li>
                        <li>Chills</li>
                        <li>Shortness of breath</li>
                        <li>Difficulty breathing</li>
                        <li>Fatigue</li>
                        <li>Muscle aches</li>
                        <li>Loss of taste or smell</li>
                        <li>Sore throat</li>
                        <li>Congestion</li>
                        <li>Runny nose</li>
                        <li>Nausea or vomitting</li>
                        <li>Diarrhea</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>For more detailed information, please visit the <a href="https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/symptoms-testing/symptoms.html" target="_blank">CDC website</a>.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
                
            <div class="w3-card w3-margin-right w3-margin-left w3-margin-top">
                <div id="question_three" class="w3-container w3-light-grey" style="cursor: pointer;"><h5>How do I get tested for Covid-19?</h5></div>
                <div id="answer_three"  class="w3-container" hidden="true">
                    <p>To get tested for the coronavirus, please contact your primary healthcare provider. When tested, you will either take a viral or antibody test. Viral tests determine if you are currently infected with Covid-19. Antibody tests check to see if you have had Covid-19 in the past.</p>
                    <p>For more detailed information, please visit the <a href="https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/symptoms-testing/testing.html" target="_blank">CDC website</a>.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        
            <div class="w3-card w3-margin-right w3-margin-left w3-margin-top">
                <div id="question_four" class="w3-container w3-light-grey" style="cursor: pointer;"><h5>What can I do to prevent getting the Coronavirus?</h5></div>
                <div id="answer_four"  class="w3-container" hidden="true">
                    <p>The CDC reccommends five high-level steps to protect yourself from Covid-19. In summary, the following steps will help prevent the spread of the virus:</p>
                    <ul class="w3-ul w3-border">
                        <li>Wear a face mask that covers your nose and mouth</li>
                        <li>Practice social distancing by staying 6 feet away from others</li>
                        <li>Get the Covid-19 vaccine when it becomes available to you</li>
                        <li>Avoid large crowds are poorly vented areas</li>
                        <li>Wash your hands frequently with soap and water</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>For more detailed information, please visit the <a href="https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/prevent-getting-sick/prevention.html" target="_blank">CDC website</a>.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="w3-card w3-margin-right w3-margin-left w3-margin-top">
                <div id="question_five" class="w3-container w3-light-grey" style="cursor: pointer;"><h5>What should I do if I get sick?</h5></div>
                <div id="answer_five"  class="w3-container" hidden="true">
                    <p></p>
                    <p>For more detailed information, please visit the <a href="https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/if-you-are-sick/steps-when-sick.html" target="_blank">CDC website</a>.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="w3-card w3-margin-right w3-margin-left w3-margin-top">
                <div id="question_six" class="w3-container w3-light-grey" style="cursor: pointer;"><h5>The pandemic is stressing me out. What can I do to help relax?</h5></div>
                <div id="answer_six"  class="w3-container" hidden="true">
                    <p>Coping with stress can be a difficult process, but there are recommendations to help manage stress and keep yourself feeling positive. To start, take a break from monitoring news stories involving Covid-19. Constantly hearing about the pandemic may be a major factor that contributes to your stress. Secondly, take care of your body by eating healthy, exercising, and getting adequate sleep. Finding time to unwind and connect (while practicing social distancing) with others to share your thoughts and feelings. If you feel as though stress levels are getting too high, please do not hesitate to reach out to a mental health provider to discuss your situation.</p>
                    <p>For more detailed information and recommendations, please visit the <a href="https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/daily-life-coping/managing-stress-anxiety.html" target="_blank">CDC website</a>.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

